The paper deals with the capacity of input-driven finite-state channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of dynamic programming and Bellman equations is also common in optimization and control theory, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also discusses input distributions with memory, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The study of finite-state channels can also be related to the field of discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on lower bounds could also be relevant to the field of computational complexity (cs.CC).
